<section>
  <div class="px-8 py-12 mx-auto md:px-12 lg:px-32 max-w-7xl lg:py-24">
    <div class="lg:gap-12 grid grid-cols-1 gap-6 lg:grid-cols-3">
      <div class="text-center lg:text-left">
        <div>
          <span
            class="text-xs text-purple-500 uppercase font-bold tracking-wide"
            >FAQ</span
          >
          <p
            class="text-4xl mt-8 font-semibold tracking-tighter text-purple-900">
            Frequent questions and answers
          </p><p class="text-gray-500 mt-4 text-base">
            Answers to commonly asked questions about our platform
          </p>
        </div>
      </div><div
        class="w-full mx-auto relative font-normal lg:col-span-2"
        x-data="{
  activeAccordion: '',
  setActiveAccordion(id) {
  this.activeAccordion = (this.activeAccordion == id) ? '' : id
  }
  }">
        <div
          class="cursor-pointer group text-gray-600 hover:text-purple-500"
          x-data="{ id: $id('accordion') }"
          :class="{ 'text-purple-900': activeAccordion==id, 'text-gray-600 hover:text-purple-500': activeAccordion!=id }">
          <button
            class="flex items-center justify-between p-4 pb-1 select-none text-left w-full text-sm lg:text-base"
            @click="setActiveAccordion(id)"
            ><span>How does end-to-end encryption work?</span>
            <svg
              class="h-5 w-5 duration-300 ease-out text-purple-500"
              fill="none"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
              stroke="currentColor"
              stroke-width="1.5"
              :class="{ '-rotate-[45deg]': activeAccordion==id }"
              ><path
                d="M12 6v12m6-6H6"
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"></path></svg
            ></button
          ><div
            x-collapse=""
            x-show="activeAccordion==id"
            style="display: none;">
            <div class="text-gray-500 p-4 pt-2 text-sm">
              End-to-end encryption ensures that only the sender and recipient
              can access the content of a message. The information is encrypted
              on the sender's device and can only be decrypted by the intended
              recipient, preventing any intermediaries, including the platform
              provider, from accessing the data.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div><div
          class="cursor-pointer group text-gray-600 hover:text-purple-500"
          x-data="{ id: $id('accordion') }"
          :class="{ 'text-purple-900': activeAccordion==id, 'text-gray-600 hover:text-purple-500': activeAccordion!=id }">
          <button
            class="flex items-center justify-between p-4 pb-1 select-none text-left w-full text-sm lg:text-base"
            @click="setActiveAccordion(id)"
            ><span
              >Can I access my encrypted data if I forget my encryption key?</span
            >
            <svg
              class="h-5 w-5 duration-300 ease-out text-purple-500"
              fill="none"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
              stroke="currentColor"
              stroke-width="1.5"
              :class="{ '-rotate-[45deg]': activeAccordion==id }"
              ><path
                d="M12 6v12m6-6H6"
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"></path></svg
            ></button
          ><div
            x-collapse=""
            x-show="activeAccordion==id"
            style="display: none;">
            <div class="text-gray-500 p-4 pt-2 text-sm">
              No, forgetting or losing your encryption key means that your
              encrypted data cannot be accessed. This is a crucial security
              measure to ensure that even if someone gains unauthorized access
              to your account, they won't be able to decrypt and view your
              messages or files.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div><div
          class="cursor-pointer group text-gray-600 hover:text-purple-500"
          x-data="{ id: $id('accordion') }"
          :class="{ 'text-purple-900': activeAccordion==id, 'text-gray-600 hover:text-purple-500': activeAccordion!=id }">
          <button
            class="flex items-center justify-between p-4 pb-1 select-none text-left w-full text-sm lg:text-base"
            @click="setActiveAccordion(id)"
            ><span
              >Are there any limitations to the self-destructing messages
              feature?</span
            >
            <svg
              class="h-5 w-5 duration-300 ease-out text-purple-500"
              fill="none"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
              stroke="currentColor"
              stroke-width="1.5"
              :class="{ '-rotate-[45deg]': activeAccordion==id }"
              ><path
                d="M12 6v12m6-6H6"
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"></path></svg
            ></button
          ><div
            x-collapse=""
            x-show="activeAccordion==id"
            style="display: none;">
            <div class="text-gray-500 p-4 pt-2 text-sm">
              Self-destructing messages are designed to automatically delete
              themselves after a specific period or upon being read by the
              recipient. However, it's important to note that the feature only
              removes the message from the devices involved in the conversation.
              Recipients may take screenshots or use other means to capture the
              content, which is beyond the platform's control.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div><div
          class="cursor-pointer group text-gray-600 hover:text-purple-500"
          x-data="{ id: $id('accordion') }"
          :class="{ 'text-purple-900': activeAccordion==id, 'text-gray-600 hover:text-purple-500': activeAccordion!=id }">
          <button
            class="flex items-center justify-between p-4 pb-1 select-none text-left w-full text-sm lg:text-base"
            @click="setActiveAccordion(id)"
            ><span
              >What happens if I enable two-factor authentication and lose my
              device?</span
            >
            <svg
              class="h-5 w-5 duration-300 ease-out text-purple-500"
              fill="none"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
              stroke="currentColor"
              stroke-width="1.5"
              :class="{ '-rotate-[45deg]': activeAccordion==id }"
              ><path
                d="M12 6v12m6-6H6"
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"></path></svg
            ></button
          ><div
            x-collapse=""
            x-show="activeAccordion==id"
            style="display: none;">
            <div class="text-gray-500 p-4 pt-2 text-sm">
              Losing your device doesn't automatically compromise your account's
              security. It's recommended to contact our support team as soon as
              possible to disable the two-factor authentication on your lost
              device and set up the authentication on your new device. This
              process will help protect your account from unauthorized access
              while ensuring you can regain access to it.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div><div
          class="cursor-pointer group text-gray-600 hover:text-purple-500"
